title: [ISSUE-2187] Fix compaction encoding bug after deserialization merge
Fix desc batchdata count bug
body:
When Batchdata is from mergeReader, the sequence of it will be in reverse. E.g. [3000, 2001], [2000, 1001], [1000, 1]

Then getMaxTimestamp should get the first but actually it got the last timestamp. That's the wrong place.

To keep it better to understand, I abstracted a new batchdata called DescReadWriteBatchdata. It's for mergeReader in `order by time desc`. And it will write data in reverse, i.e. the sequence will be [1, 1000], [1001, 2000], [2001, 3000]

title: [IOTDB-1081] New TsFile Format
body:
We find that the former tsfile format waste some disk space, some information was stored duplicately and some legacy fields are no longer useful.

So I design a new TsFile format to make our tsfile more dense. The design document link is https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/IOTDB/New+TsFile+Format

[IOTDB-1011] Memtable sort in query
body:
Now a query will copy and sort TV list from memtable but never put it back to memtable. That's means when another query come, same data will be sort again. So we should put it back to memtable.

JIRA: https://issues.apache.org/jira/projects/IOTDB/issues/IOTDB-1011
Design: https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=165225810
Test report: https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/IOTDB/Sort+Memtable+in+inserting+test+report

title: To rel/0.11Fix modules can not be found when using pypi  to pack client-py
body:
In this PR, the client-py package structure will be:
.
 iotdb
  Session.py
  __init__.py
  thrift
   __init__.py
   cluster
    RaftService-remote
    RaftService.py
    TSDataService-remote
    TSDataService.py
    TSMetaService-remote
    TSMetaService.py
    __init__.py
    constants.py
    ttypes.py
   rpc
    TSIService-remote
    TSIService.py
    __init__.py
    constants.py
    ttypes.py
   sync
       SyncService-remote
       SyncService.py
       __init__.py
       constants.py
       ttypes.py
  utils
      Field.py
      IoTDBConstants.py
      IoTDBRpcDataSet.py
      RowRecord.py
      SessionDataSet.py
      Tablet.py
     __init__.py

So, after `pip3 install apache-iotdb`,  just use `from iotdb.Session import Session` 
( and  `from iotdb.utils import Tablet` if you need some advanced APIs).

Thank @JulianFeinauer  and @SilverNarcissus 's contribution.
